INSERT INTO `policiesMaster` VALUES (1,'Financial policy','<div class=\"modal-body\">     <p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>I. Insurance Coverage (through Aetna, Cigna and Cardinal Care):</strong></span></p>     <p>Savant Care is in the process of getting contracted with Aetna, Cigna and Cardinal Care (the Stanford Student Health branch of Managed Health Network).  This process should be completed by September 1<sup>st</sup>, 2014.  If you have any of the aforementioned insurances and are interested in utilizing their coverage for mental health treatment, it is very important that you find out exactly what mental health services your particular policy covers.  You should carefully read the plugin in your insurance coverage booklet that describes mental health services.  If you have questions about the coverage, call your plan administrator.  Our staff will provide you with assistance in receiving the benefits to which you are entitled; however <strong>you</strong> (not your insurance company) are responsible for full payment of your bill.  If your failure to comply with your insurance company\'s requirements regarding choice of providers, authorization or other issues results in the denial of claims, you will be responsible for paying in full.  If your coverage changes, it is your responsibility to notify your provider and to comply with your new policy.  Once Savant Care has all of the information about your insurance coverage, your psychiatrist will discuss what you can expect to accomplish with the benefits that are available and what will happen if they run out before you feel ready to end your treatment.  It is important to remember that you always have the right to pay for services out of pocket to avoid the potential issues described above (unless this is prohibited by your insurance contract). </p>     <p>You should be aware that your insurance company requires a clinical diagnosis and information about the services provided to you.  Sometimes, your physician must provide additional clinical information such as treatment plans or summaries, or copies of your entire Clinical Record.  In such situations, every effort will be made to release only the minimum information about you that is necessary for the purpose requested.  This information will become part of the insurance company\'s records. Though all insurance companies claim to keep such information confidential, we have no control over what they do with it once it is in their hands. </p>     <p></p>     <p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>II. Out-of-Pocket Payment Options:</strong></span></p>     <p><strong>REGULAR TRACK:</strong> If you choose the <strong>Regular Track</strong>, you will be able to obtain clinic appointments at the next available appointment during business hours.  You should expect returned phone calls or email response by our clinic coordinator within 1 business day.  Urgent phone calls or emails will be forwarded to your psychiatrist or psychotherapist, and you will receive a response from him/her as soon as possible (at least within at least 2 business days).</p>     <table cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"center\" border=\"1\">         <thead>             <tr>                 <th>Encounter Type</th>                 <th>Time Spent</th>                 <th>Fee</th>             </tr>         </thead>         <tbody>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Initial Appointment</td>                 <td>60-75 minutes face-to-face, 15 minutes for documentation and other management tasks by the provider</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$400</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Standard Medication Follow-Up</td>                 <td>20 minutes face-to-face, 10 minutes for documentation and other management tasks by the provider</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$200</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Standard Psychotherapy Session</td>                 <td>45 minutes face-to-face, 15 minutes for documentation by the provider</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$300</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Other</td>                 <td>Telephone calls with provider >5 minutes, email communication with provider requiring >5 minutes of provider\'s time, phone communication by provider with others (other providers or family members) on behalf of patient, documentation requests requiring >5 minutes of provider\'s time</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$5/minute after the first 5 minutes</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Concierge Treatment (based on necessity if deemed appropriate by consulting psychiatrist and by request only)</td>                 <td>45 minute in-home or in-hospital (if admitted) face-to-face visit with provider within 10 mile radius within 7 business days of the request </td>                 <td align=\"center\">$800</td>             </tr>         </tbody>     </table>     <p></p>     <p><strong>CONCIERGE TRACK:</strong> If you choose the <strong>Concierge Track</strong>, you will be given first priority for appointment times.  This means you will have access to the evening and weekend times of our providers, in addition to their regular clinic business hours.  You will also be able to obtain a clinic appointment or phone session either on the same day or within 1 business day of your request with your provider.  You will also have the option of obtaining a home or in-hospital (if admitted) based on necessity within at least 2 business days of your request. You should expect returned phone calls or email responses directly from your provider within at least 4 business hours. </p>     <table cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"center\" border=\"1\">         <thead>             <tr>                 <th>Encounter Type</th>                 <th>Time Spent</th>                 <th>Fee</th>             </tr>         </thead>         <tbody>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Initial Appointment</td>                 <td>60-75 minutes face-to-face, 15 minutes for documentation and other management tasks by the provider</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$700</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Standard Medication Follow-Up (Phone or In-Clinic)</td>                 <td>20 minutes face-to-face, 10 minutes for documentation and other management tasks by the provider</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$400</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Standard Psychotherapy Session (Phone or In-Clinic)</td>                 <td>45 minutes face-to-face, 15 minutes for documentation by the provider</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$600</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">In-Home of In-Hospital Visits (based on necessity, as deemed appropriate by consulting Psychiatrist)</td>                 <td>45 minute in-home or in-hospital (if admitted) face-to-face visit with provider within 10 mile radius within 2 business days of the request</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$800</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Other</td>                 <td>Telephone calls with provider >5 minutes, email communication with provider requiring >5 minutes of provider\'s time, phone communication by provider with others (other providers or family members) on behalf of patient, documentation requests requiring >5 minutes of provider\'s time</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$5/minute after the first 5 minutes</td>             </tr>         </tbody>     </table>     <p><strong>Note that if you seek reimbursement from an insurer, Savant Care can submit claims on your behalf at your request without any extra charge.</strong>  Insurers may only partially reimburse you; contact your insurer for details on your out-of-network coverage.  You should be aware that, in order for you to obtain reimbursement, your insurance company requires a clinical diagnosis and information about the services provided to you.  Sometimes, your physician must provide additional clinical information such as treatment plans or summaries, or copies of your entire Clinical Record.  In such situations, every effort will be made to release only the minimum information about you that is necessary for the purpose requested.  This information will become part of the insurance company\'s records. Though all insurance companies claim to keep such information confidential, we have no control over what they do with it once it is in their hands.</p> <p>Savant Care may offer treatment at discounted rates if you provide proof of financial need.</p>  </div>',0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(2,'Privacy policy','<div class=\"modal-body\">      <p>Savant Care works in accordance with the HIPPA laws. These laws protect the confidentiality of all communications between a patient and psychiatrist/psychotherapist.  Several types of communications and the consent they require are discussed below.</p>     <p>     <ol type=\"1\">         <li>Generally, information about your treatment can be released to others only if you sign a written Release of Information form.</li>         <li>There are other situations, however, that require only that you provide written, advance consent.  Your signature on this Agreement provides consent for the following:             <ul type=\"i\">                 <li>Your psychiatrist may occasionally find it helpful to consult other health and mental health professionals about a case. During a consultation, every effort is made to avoid revealing your identity.  The other professionals are also legally bound to keep the information confidential.  You will not be told about these consultations unless your therapist feels it is important to your work together</li>                 <li>Savant Care employs other mental health professionals and administrative staff to run the practice.  As a result, some protected information may be shared with these individuals for both clinical and administrative purposes, such as scheduling, billing, and quality assurance.  All of the mental health professionals and staff are bound by the same rules of confidentiality and all staff members have undergone the appropriate HIPPA training to protect your privacy.  No staff member will release any information outside of the practice without the permission of a professional staff member.</li>                 <li>Savant Care has contracts with other vendors such as software providers and an accountant.  Typically no protected health information is shared with them. As required by HIPAA laws, we have a formal business associate contract with these outside businesses, in which they promise to maintain the confidentiality of any such data except as specifically allowed in the contract or otherwise required by law.</li>                 <li>Disclosures required by health insurers or to collect overdue fees are discussed in the Financial Policies.</li>                 <li>If your psychiatrist believes that you present an imminent danger to your health or safety, he/she may be obligated to seek hospitalization for you or to contact family members or others who can help provide assistance.</li>             </ul>         </li>         <li>There are also some situations where psychiatrists are permitted or required to disclose information without either your consent or authorization:             <ul type=\"i\">                 <li>If you are involved in a court proceeding and a request is made for information concerning the professional services provided to you, such information is protected by the psychiatrist-patient privilege law.  Information cannot be provided without your written authorization or a court order.  If you are involved in or contemplating litigation, you should consult with your attorney to determine whether a court would be likely to order us to disclose information</li>                 <li>If a government agency is requesting the information for health oversight activities, we may be required to provide it for them</li>                 <li>If a patient files a complaint or a lawsuit against a psychiatrist, that psychiatrist may disclose relevant information regarding that patient in order to defend him/herself.</li>                 <li>If a patient files a worker\'s compensation claim, and services are being compensated through workers compensation benefits, a psychiatrist must, upon appropriate request, provide a copy of the patient\'s record to the patient\'s employer.</li>             </ul>         </li>         <li>In addition, there are some situations in which psychiatrists are legally obligated to take actions which are necessary to attempt to protect others from harm and which may require revealing some information about a patient\'s treatment.             <ul type=\"i\">                 <li>If there is a cause to suspect that a child under 18 is abused or neglected, or reasonable cause to believe that a disabled adult or elderly individual is in need of protective services, the law requires that a report be filed with the county.  Once such a report is filed, additional information may be required.</li>                 <li>If there is reasons to believe that a client present imminent danger to the health and safety of another, we may be required to disclose information in order to take protective actions, including initiating hospitalization, warning the potential victim, if identifiable and or calling the police.</li>             </ul>         </li>     </ol>     </p>     <p>The laws governing confidentiality can be quite complex.  It is important that any questions or concerns that you may have now or in the future be discussed. In some cases, formal legal advice may be needed. </p>     <p>Of note, email communication can be relatively easily accessed by unauthorized people, and thus, the privacy and confidentiality of such communication can be easily compromised.  In rare cases, faxes may be sent erroneously to the wrong address.  Please use email for non-clinical issues only and please do not use email or faxes in emergency situations!</p>     <p><strong>I am aware of and agree to each of the above statements and consent to treatment.</strong></p> </div>',0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(3,'Treatment contract','<div class=\"modal-body\">          <p></p>     <p><strong>Initial Consultation:</strong>  The first appointment is a 60-75-minute face-to-face assessment. All appropriate intake paperwork must be completed prior to your first appointment.  During the first session, the Savant Care provider will obtain a comprehensive history and determine whether our clinic can meet your treatment needs.  This session is also an opportunity for both you and the provider to assess your mutual compatibility for an ongoing treatment relationship.  Depending on the complexity of your case, the initial evaluation may exceed 75 minutes, in which case a second 45-minute appointment will be made to complete the assessment and make treatment recommendations. Medications may or may not be prescribed during the initial appointment(s). </p>     <p><strong>Privacy:</strong> Savant Care will not disclose details of your treatment nor your medical record to third parties without your written approval.  I work in accordance with the HIPPA laws.  You understand your rights under the HIPPA laws, can discuss these with me at anytime and have received notice of privacy policies.</p>     <p><strong>Payment:</strong> Credit card information will be obtained prior to your first appointment at Savant Care.  The provided credit card will be charged at the beginning of each clinic appointment, home visit, and/or in-hospital visit with your Savant Care provider according to the fee structure outlined in the Financial Policies.  If you have insurance, then we well charge the co-pay or appropriate amount if you have not met your deductible before your appointment. You have read and agree to the Financial Policies.  If you seek reimbursement from an insurer, Savant Care can submit claims on your behalf at your request (see Financial Policies for further information).</p>     <p><strong>Late, Missed Appointment and Cancellation Policies:</strong>  Sessions start on time and end on time. If you arrive too late to allow time for proper care, you may be asked to reschedule.  If you are more than 15 minutes late to your appointment, you will be asked to reschedule.  Missed appointments prevent you from receiving required care and prevent the doctor from providing that care.  They also prevent another person from care during that time.  As a result, <strong>you will be financially responsible for the full session fee if you miss your appointment or fail to cancel your appointment within at least 3 business days of the appointment.</strong>  If an appointment must be missed for whatever reason, <strong>you have the option of rescheduling your appointment within the same week of the missed appointment depending on the doctor\'s availability; in this scenario, you will not be charged for a missed appointment.</strong> </p>     <p><strong>Disclosures:</strong> If you are a danger to yourself or others or if I suspect abuse towards a child, disabled adult or the elderly, I am ethically and legally required to report it to the appropriate authorities.</p>     <p><strong>Legal Issues:</strong> In order to safeguard the process of treatment, I do not testify in court nor participate in disability evaluations.  I do not accept gifts from patients nor participate in business deals with patients. </p>     <p><strong>Clinic discharge policy:</strong>  Savant Care reserves the right to discharge patients from the clinic under the following conditions: multiple missed appointments and patient nonadherence to the treatment plan.  If you fail to follow up with your provider for more than 6 months without prior authorization or have >3 cancellations/missed appointments within a 12 month period, it will be considered failure to comply with the treatment plan and you will be automatically discharged from Savant Care as a patient. You may return to clinic with authorization from a provider and resume receiving care at Savant Care if you wish to do so. Discharged patients will always be provided with appropriate referrals.</p>     <p>Our clinic policies are subject to change and you will be notified of these changes as they arise. Savant care reserves the right to make changes to clinic policies at any time. This contract will be valid for 3 years.</p>     <p><strong>I understand and agree to each of the above statements and consent to treatment.</strong></p>           </div>',0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(5,'Privacy policy','<div class=\"modal-body\">      <p>Savant Care works in accordance with the HIPPA laws. These laws protect the confidentiality of all communications between a patient and psychiatrist/psychotherapist.  Several types of communications and the consent they require are discussed below.</p>     <p>     <ol type=\"1\">         <li>Generally, information about your treatment can be released to others only if you sign a written Release of Information form.</li>         <li>There are other situations, however, that require only that you provide written, advance consent.  Your signature on this Agreement provides consent for the following:             <ul type=\"i\">                 <li>Your psychiatrist may occasionally find it helpful to consult other health and mental health professionals about a case. During a consultation, every effort is made to avoid revealing your identity.  The other professionals are also legally bound to keep the information confidential.  You will not be told about these consultations unles