e purpose requested. This information will become part of the insurance company\'s records. Though all insurance companies claim to keep such information confidential, we have no control over what they do with it once it is in their hands.<br></p><p>Savant Care may offer treatment at discounted rates if you provide proof of financial need.</p><p><strong>C. INSURANCE TRACK</strong><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">:</span></p><p>The physicians at Savant Care are currently contracted with MHN/Healtnet, &nbsp;Aetna, Tricare and Medicare, and are <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">accepting new patients</span>. &nbsp;If you are a member of these insurances, and are interested in utilizing your coverage for mental health treatment, it is very important that you find out exactly what mental health services your particular policy covers. You should carefully read the section in your insurance coverage booklet that describes mental health services. &nbsp;If you have questions about the coverage, call your plan administrator. &nbsp;Our &nbsp;staff will provide you with assistance in receiving the benefits to which you are entitled; however you (not your insurance company) are responsible for full payment of your bill. &nbsp;If your failure to comply with your insurance companys requirements regarding choice of providers, authorization, or other issues resulting in the denial of claims, you will be responsible for paying in full. &nbsp;If your coverage changes, it is your responsibility to notify your provider and to comply with your new policy. &nbsp;</p><p>Once Savant Care has all of the information about your insurance coverage, your psychiatrist will discuss what you can expect to accomplish with the benefits that are available and what will happen if they run out before you feel ready to end your treatment. &nbsp;It is important to remember that you always have the right to pay for services out of pocket to avoid the potential issues described above (unless this is pro