: solid; border-top-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-bottom-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-left-color: rgb(204, 204, 204); border-radius: 4px 0px 0px 4px; background-color: rgb(238, 238, 238);\">Date :</span><input class=\"form-control col-sm-6 ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required\" type=\"date\" name=\"dateInput\" ng-required=\"!policyobj.signdate\" close-text=\"Close\" data-ng-model=\"policyobj.signdate\" required=\"required\" aria-invalid=\"true\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 34px; font-family: Roboto, \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; margin: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; position: relative; min-height: 1px; padding: 6px 12px; float: left; width: 795px; display: table-cell; height: 34px; border: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); border-radius: 0px 4px 4px 0px; box-shadow: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0745098) 0px 1px 1px inset; transition: border-color 0.15s ease-in-out, box-shadow 0.15s ease-in-out; outline: 0px; background-image: none;\"></div></div></div></form> </div>',23,'2016-03-22 01:18:50',NULL,NULL),(34,'Financial policy','<div class=\"modal-body\">     <p><strong>A. REGULAR TRACK: </strong>If you choose the <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Regular Track</span>, we will be able to obtain clinic appointments at the next available appointment during business hours. You should expect returned phone calls or email response by our clinic co-ordinator within 1 business day. Urgent phone calls or emails will be forwarded to your psychiatrist or psychotherapist, and you will receive a response from him / her as soon as possible, (at least within 2 business days).</p><p></p><table cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"center\" border=\"1\"><thead><tr><th>Encounter Type</th>                 <th>Time Spent</th>                 <th>Fee</th>             </tr>         </thead>         <tbody>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Initial Appointment (INTAKE)</td>                 <td>60-75 minutes face-to-face, 15 minutes for documentation and other management tasks by the provider.<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>In case the initial assessment takes longer than 75 minutes ( due to the complexity of your condition), then we may charge you an additional fee.&nbsp;<br><br></td>                 <td align=\"center\">$400</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Standard Medication Follow-Up</td>                 <td>20 minutes face-to-face, 10 minutes for documentation and other management tasks by the provider.</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$200</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Standard Psychotherapy Session</td>                 <td>45 minutes face-to-face.</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$300</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Other</td>                 <td>- Telephone calls with provider and email communications with provider requiring significant amount of time will be treated as consultation with the provider and will be charged as such.&nbsp;<br>- Co-ordination of care on behalf of patient requiring significant amount of time may incur an extra fee.&nbsp;<br>- Disability documentation and other extraneous documentation will incur extra fee.&nbsp;</td>                 <td align=\"center\"><br></td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Concierge Treatment (based on necessity if deemed appropriate by consulting psychiatrist and by request only)</td>                 <td>45 minute in-home or in-hospital (if admitted) face-to-face visit with provider within 10 mile radius within 7 business days of the request </td>                 <td align=\"center\">$800</td>             </tr>         </tbody>     </table>     <p></p>     <p><strong>B. CONCIERGE TRACK:</strong> If you choose the <strong>Concierge Track</strong>, you will be given first priority for appointment times.  This means you will have access to the evening and weekend times of our providers, in addition to their regular clinic business hours.  You will also be able to obtain a clinic appointment or phone session either on the same day or within 1 business day of your request with your provider.  You will also have the option of obtaining a home or in-hospital (if admitted) based on necessity within at least 2 business days of your request. You should expect returned phone calls or email responses directly from your provider within at least 4 business hours. </p>     <table cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"center\" border=\"1\">         <thead>             <tr>                 <th>Encounter Type</th>                 <th>Time Spent</th>                 <th>Fee</th>             </tr>         </thead>         <tbody>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Initial Appointment</td>                 <td>60-75 minutes face-to-face, 15 minutes for documentation and other management tasks by the provider</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$700</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Standard Medication Follow-Up (Phone or In-Clinic)</td>                 <td>20 minutes face-to-face, 10 minutes for documentation and other management tasks by the provider</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$400</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Standard Psychotherapy Session (Phone or In-Clinic)</td>                 <td>45 minutes face-to-face, 15 minutes for documentation by the provider</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$600</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">In-Home or In-Hospital Visits (based on necessity, as deemed appropriate by consulting Psychiatrist)</td>                 <td>45 minute in-home or in-hospital (if admitted) face-to-face visit with provider within 10 mile radius within 2 business days of the request</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$800</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Other</td>                 <td>Telephone calls with or on behalf of the patient, email communications, and documentation requests requiring substantial amount of providers time.&nbsp;</td>                 <td align=\"center\">TBD</td>             </tr>         </tbody>     </table>     <p><strong>Note that if you seek reimbursement from an insurer, Savant Care can submit claims on your behalf at your request without any extra charge.</strong>&nbsp;Insurers may only partially reimburse you; contact your insurer for details on your out-of-network coverage. You should be aware that, in order for you to obtain reimbursement, your insurance company requires a clinical diagnosis and information about the services provided to you. Sometimes, your physician must provide additional clinical information such as treatment plans or summaries, or copies of your entire Clinical Record. In such situations, every effort will be made to release only the minimum information about you that is necessary for the purpose requested. This information will become part of the insurance company\'s records. Though all insurance companies claim to keep such information confidential, we have no control over what they do with it once it is in their hands.<br></p><p>Savant Care may offer treatment at discounted rates if you provide proof of financial need.</p><p><strong>C. INSURANCE TRACK</strong><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">:</span></p><p>The physicians at Savant Care are currently contracted with MHN, Anthem Blue Cross Of California, Blue Shield of California, &nbsp;Aetna, Tricare, Medicare, and Cardinal Care--and are <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">accepting new patients</span>. &nbsp;If you are a member of these insurances, and are interested in utilizing your coverage for mental health treatment, it is very important that you find out exactly what mental health services your particular policy covers. You should carefully read the section in your insurance coverage booklet that describes mental health services. &nbsp;If you have questions about the coverage, call your plan administrator. &nbsp;Our &nbsp;staff will provide you with assistance in receiving the benefits to which you are entitled; however you (not your insurance company) are responsible for full payment of your bill. &nbsp;If your failure to comply with your insurance companys requirements regarding choice of providers, authorization, or other issues resulting in the denial of claims, you will be responsible for paying in full. &nbsp;If your coverage changes, it is your responsibility to notify your provider and to comply with your new policy. &nbsp;In-Network participation by SC and it\'s providers are subject to change without notice.&nbsp;</p><p>Once Savant Care has all of the information about your insurance coverage, your psychiatrist will discuss what you can expect to accomplish with the benefits that are available and what will happen if they run out before you feel ready to end your treatment. &nbsp;It is important to remember that you always have the right to pay for services out of pocket to avoid the potential issues described above (unless this is prohibited by your insurance contract).&nbsp;</p><p>You should be aware that your insurance company requires a clinical diagnosis and information about the services provided to you. &nbsp;Sometimes, your physician must provide additional clinical information such as treatment plans or summaries, or copies of your entire Clinical Record. &nbsp;In such situations, every effort will be made to release only the minimum information about you that is necessary for the purpose requested. &nbsp;This information will become part of the insurance companys records. Though all insurance companies claim to keep such information confidential, we have no control over what they do with it once it is in their hands. &nbsp;</p><p>Initial visits will be 45 minutes. &nbsp;Follow up appointments for medication management will be 15-20 minutes and for psychotherapy +/- medication management will be 45 minutes.&nbsp;</p><p>It is our policy to charge on a prorated basis for other professional services such as extended telephone consultations, report writing, meeting attendance, disability paperwork, letter writing, and preparation of treatment summaries. You are responsible for any charges not covered by your insurance carrier including any co-payments required by your policy.</p><p><strong>Cancellation Policies:&nbsp;</strong>sessions start on time and end on time. If you arrive too late to allow time for proper care, you may be asked to reschedule. If you are more than 15 minutes late to your appointment, you will be asked to reschedule. Missed appointments prevent you from receiving required care and prevent the doctor from providing that care. It also prevents another person from receiving care during that time. As a result,&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">you will be financially responsible for $250 cancellation fee if you miss your initial appointment&nbsp;or fail to cancel it within at least 3 business days of the appointment. You will be financially responsible for the full session fee. If you miss a follow up appointment or fail to cancel it within at least 3 business days of the appointment.&nbsp;</span>If an appointment must be missed for whatever reasons,&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">you have the option of rescheduling your appointment within the same week of the missed appointment depending on the doctor\'s&nbsp;availability. In this scenario, you will not be charged for a missed appointment.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">&nbsp;Note: Insurance does NOT cover missed appointments.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note that if you are having difficulties paying your balance, or feel we may have billed you in error, please contact our office for resolution before initiating action with your financial institution. Failure to notify our office for resolution before initiating a dispute or chargeback will result in a fee of $50 for each&nbsp;occurrence.&nbsp;</span></p>  </div>',24,'2016-03-25 10:55:00',NULL,NULL),(35,'Treatment contract','<div class=\"modal-body\">          <p></p>     <p><strong>Initial Consultation:</strong>  The first appointment is a 60-75-minute face-to-face assessment. All appropriate intake paperwork must be completed prior to your first appointment.  During the first session, the Savant Care provider will obtain a comprehensive history and determine whether our clinic can meet your treatment needs.  This session is also an opportunity for both you and the provider to assess your mutual compatibility for an ongoing treatment relationship.  Depending on the complexity of your case, the initial evaluation may exceed 75 minutes, in which case a second 45-minute appointment will be made to complete the assessment and make treatment recommendations. Medications may or may not be prescribed during the initial appointment(s). An initial consult with a provider is not the establishment of a provider-patient relationship.&nbsp;</p>     <p><strong>Privacy:</strong> Savant Care will not disclose details of your treatment nor your medical record to third parties without your written approval.  I work in accordance with the HIPPA laws.  You understand your rights under the HIPPA laws, can discuss these with me at anytime and have received notice of privacy policies.</p>     <p><strong>Payment:</strong> Credit card information or bank information will be obtained prior to your first appointment at Savant Care. You or your payer will be charged at the beginning of each clinic appointment, home visit and/or in-hospital visit with your Savant Care provider according to the fee structure outlined in the financial policies. If you have insurance, then we will charge the appropriate amount. If you seek reimbursement from an insurer, Savant Care can submit claims on your behalf at your request (see financial policies for further information).&nbsp;</p>     <p><strong>Late, Missed Appointment and Cancellation Policies:</strong>  Sessions start on time and end on time. If you arrive too late to allow time for proper care, you may be asked to reschedule.  If you are more than 15 minutes late to your appointment, you will be asked to reschedule.  Missed appointments prevent you from receiving required care and prevent the doctor from providing that care.  They also prevent another person from care during that time.  As a result, <strong>you will be financially responsible for the full session fee if you miss your appointment or fail to cancel your appointment within at least 3 business days of the appointment.</strong>  If an appointment must be missed for whatever reason, <strong>you have the option of rescheduling your appointment within the same week of the missed appointment depending on the doctor\'s availability; in this scenario, you will not be charged for a missed appointment.</strong> </p>     <p><strong>Disclosures:</strong> If you are a danger to yourself or others or if I suspect abuse towards a child, disabled adult or the elderly, I am ethically and legally required to report it to the appropriate authorities.</p>     <p><strong>Legal Issues:</strong> In order to safeguard the process of treatment, our providers do not testify in court. I do not accept gifts from patients nor participate in business deals with patients. </p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Controlled substance policy:</span>&nbsp;Please take extra precaution when handling a prescription of controlled substances (as per DEA, definition of a controlled substance) such as Opiates, Stimulants, Sedative-Hypnotic agents etc. we reserve the rights to refuse giving early refills or to replace lost prescriptions. If prescriptions are lost or you have run out early more than once in 1 year period we may decide to discharge you from the clinic if abuse or misuse is suspected. If there is any evidence that you have been receiving controlled prescription without informing your Savant Care provider from multiple physicians, we reserve the right to discharge you from the clinic immediately. In such case, if you are concerned for your health or safety, you should visit the nearest emergency room or call 911.&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Clinic discharge policy:</strong>  Savant Care reserves the right to discharge patients from the clinic under the following conditions, including but, not limited to:&nbsp;</p><p></p><ul><li>multiple missed appointments&nbsp;</li><li>patient non-adherence to the treatment plan.&nbsp;</li><li>Non-payment of fee owed to the providers of Savant Care.&nbsp;</li><li>&nbsp;If you fail to follow up with your provider for more than 6 months without prior authorization or have &gt;3 cancellations/missed appointments within a 12 month period, it will be considered failure to comply with the treatment plan and you will be automatically discharged from Savant Care as a patient. You may return to clinic with authorization from a provider and resume receiving care at Savant Care if you wish to do so. If there is any evidence that you have been receiving controlled prescriptions without informing your Savant Care provider from multiple physicians, we reserve the right to discharge from the clinic immediately.&nbsp;<br></li><li>If prescriptions are lost or you have run out early more than once in a 1 year period, we may decide to discharge you from the clinic if abuse or misuse is suspected.&nbsp;</li><li>If there is any evidence that you have been receiving controlled prescriptions from multiple physicians without informing your Savant Care provider, we reserve the right to discharge from the clinic immediately.&nbsp;</li></ul><p></p>     <p>Our clinic policies are subject to change and you will be notified of these changes as they arise. Savant care reserves the right to make changes to clinic policies at any time. This contract will be valid for 3 years.</p><p><strong>I understand that I will be financially&nbsp;responsible&nbsp;for the full session fee if I miss my appointment or fail to cancel my intake of follow up appointment withint at least 3 business days of the appointment.&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>&nbsp;I have acknowledged the clinic discharge policy outlined above.</strong></p><p><strong><br></strong></p><p><strong><br></strong></p>           </div>',5,'2016-04-19 11:29:45',NULL,NULL),(36,'Financial policy','<div class=\"modal-body\">     <p><strong>A. REGULAR TRACK: </strong>If you choose the <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Regular Track</span>, we will be able to obtain clinic appointments at the next available appointment during business hours. You should expect returned phone calls or email response by our clinic co-ordinator within 1 business day. Urgent phone calls or emails will be forwarded to your psychiatrist or psychotherapist, and you will receive a response from him / her as soon as possible, (at least within 2 business days).</p><p></p><table cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"center\" border=\"1\"><thead><tr><th>Encounter Type</th>                 <th>Time Spent</th>                 <th>Fee</th>             </tr>         </thead>         <tbody>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Initial Appointment (INTAKE)</td>                 <td>60-75 minutes face-to-face, 15 minutes for documentation and other management tasks by the provider.<br>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>In case the initial assessment takes longer than 75 minutes ( due to the complexity of your condition), then we may charge you an additional fee.&nbsp;<br><br></td>       