er what they do with it once it is in their hands.</p><p><strong>Cancellation Policies:&nbsp;</strong>sessions start on time and end on time. If you arrive too late to allow time for proper care, you may be asked to reschedule. If you are more than 15 minutes late to your appointment, you will be asked to reschedule. Missed appointments prevent you from receiving required care and prevent the doctor from providing that care. It also prevents another person from receiving care during that time. As a result,&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">you will be financially responsible for $250 cancellation fee if you miss your initial appointment&nbsp;or fail to cancel it within at least 3 business days of the appointment. You will be financially responsible for the full session fee. If you miss a follow up appointment or fail to cancel it within at least 3 business days of the appointment.&nbsp;</span>If an appointment must be missed for whatever reasons,&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">you have the option of rescheduling your appointment within the same week of the missed appointment depending on the doctor\'s&nbsp;availability. In this scenario, you will not be charged for a missed appointment.&nbsp;</span><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note: </span>Insurance does NOT cover missed appointments.&nbsp;<br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Payment Methods:&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;Bank ACH&nbsp;(direct deposit) as this proves to be the lowest cost solution for patients.&nbsp;&nbsp;Credit Cards&nbsp;and&nbsp;Debit Cards&nbsp;are accepted, but any fees charged by your credit card company will be passed to you. As of August 1st,2016, the fee is 4%.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-style: italic;\">CHECKS and CASH are accepted, but are not preferred. If check or cash is provided for payment, a $50 paper check/cash handling fee applies for each check or cash transaction.&nbsp;</span></p><p>All charges to Credit/Debit Cards and ACH are performed up to 3 business days BEFORE your appointment.&nbsp;</p><p>All payments made will first be applied to any prior unpaid balances before current charges.&nbsp;<br></p><p>By providing your details and signing this policy below, you are authorizing Savant Care to charge your account details provided and agree to pay all applicable charges outstanding on your patient account.</p><p>Savant Care may offer treatment at discounted rates if you provide proof of financial need. &nbsp;Please submit your requests to Savant Care\'s finance team. <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">NOTE:&nbsp;PROVIDERS CAN NOT GRANT DISCOUNTS NOR \'NEGOTIATE\' LOWER RATES WITH PATIENTS.<br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Savant Care and it\'s providers DO NOT accept or participate in MEDI-CAL or MEDICAID programs. If you have this as a secondary insurance, you will be solely responsible for all charges not paid or covered by your primary insurance.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Savant Care is not liable or responsible for any disputes or issues you may have with your insurer concerning your plan\'s deductible, coinsurance, or out-of-pocket limits. It is the patient\'s responsibility to contact their insurance for inquiries or concerns related to their applicable benefits.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note that if you are having difficulties paying your balance, or feel we may have billed you in error, please contact our office for resolution before initiating action with your financial institution. Failure to notify our office for resolution before initiating a dispute or chargeback will result in a fee of $50 for each&nbsp;occurrence.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Other services:&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">For requests for paperwork that is not available electronically and not from a medical provider (i.e. Explanation of benefits, invoices above and beyond what\'s available on your Myhealth Portal, or research requests for the office staff), a surcharge of $50 will be applied for each occurrence up to 1 hour of office staff\'s time.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">An addition fee of $25/hour will be applied beyond the first hour per occurrence.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p>  </div>',34,'2016-08-26 09:15:58',NULL,NULL),(49,'Privacy policy','<div class=\"modal-body\">      <p>Savant Care works in accordance with the HIPAA laws. These laws protect the confidentiality of all communications between a patient and psychiatrist/psychotherapist.  Several types of communications and the consent they require are discussed below.</p>     <p>     </p><ol type=\"1\">         <li>Generally, information about your treatment can be released to others only if you sign a written Release of Information form.</li>         <li>There are other situations, however, that require only that you provide written, advance consent.  Your signature on this Agreement provides consent for the following:             <ul type=\"i\">                 <li>Your psychiatrist may occasionally find it helpful to consult other health and mental health professionals about a case. During a consultation, every effort is made to avoid revealing your identity.  The other professionals are also legally bound to keep the information confidential.  You will not be told about these consultations unless your therapist feels it is important to your work together</li>                 <li>Savant Care employs other mental health professionals and administrative staff to run the practice.  As a result, some protected information may be shared with these individuals for both clinical and administrative purposes, such as scheduling, billing, and quality assurance. All of the mental health professionals and staff are bound by the same rules of confidentiality and all staff members have undergone the appropriate HIPAA training to protect your privacy.  No staff member will release any information outside of the practice without the permission of a professional staff member.</li><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">The mental health professionals on your care team (your Savant Care doctor, your Savant Care therapist, etc) collaborate closely on clinical matters to ensure the best possible care.</span></li>                 <li>Savant Care has contracts with other vendors such as software providers and an accountant.  Typically no protected health information is shared with them. As required by HIPAA laws, we have a formal business associate contract with these outside businesses, in which they promise to maintain the confidentiality of any such data except as specifically allowed in the contract or otherwise required by law.</li>                 <li>Disclosures required by health insurers or to collect overdue fees are discussed in the Financial Policies.</li>                 <li>If your psychiatrist believes that you present an imminent danger to your health or safety, he/she may be obligated to seek hospitalization for you or to contact family members or others who can help provide assistance.</li>             </ul>         </li>         <li>There are also some situations where psychiatrists are permitted or required to disclose information without either your consent or authorization:             <ul type=\"i\">                 <li>If you are involved in a court proceeding and a request is made for information concerning the professional services provided to you, such information is protected by the psychiatrist-patient privilege law.  Information cannot be provided without your written authorization or a court order.  If you are involved in or contemplating litigation, you should consult with your attorney to determine whether a court would be likely to order us to disclose information</li>                 <li>If a government agency is requesting the information for health oversight activities, we may be required to provide it for them</li>                 <li>If a patient files a complaint or a lawsuit against a psychiatrist, that psychiatrist may disclose relevant information regarding that patient in order to defend him/herself.</li>                 <li>If a patient files a worker\'s compensation claim, and services are being compensated through workers compensation benefits, a psychiatrist must, upon appropriate request, provide a copy of the patient\'s record to the patient\'s employer.</li>             </ul>         </li>         <li>In addition, there are some situations in which psychiatrists are legally obligated to take actions which are necessary to attempt to protect others from harm and which may require revealing some information about a patient\'s treatment.             <ul type=\"i\">                 <li>If there is a cause to suspect that a child under 18 is abused or neglected, or reasonable cause to believe that a disabled adult or elderly individual is in need of protective services, the law requires that a report be filed with the county.  Once such a report is filed, additional information may be required.</li>                 <li>If there is reasons to believe that a client present imminent danger to the health and safety of another, we may be required to disclose information in order to take protective actions, including initiating hospitalization, warning the potential victim, if identifiable and or calling the police.</li>             </ul>         </li>     </ol>     <p></p>     <p>The laws governing confidentiality can be quite complex.  It is important that any questions or concerns that you may have now or in the future be discussed. In some cases, formal legal advice may be needed. </p>     <p>Of note, email communication can be relatively easily accessed by unauthorized people, and thus, the privacy and confidentiality of such communication can be easily compromised.  In rare cases, faxes may be sent erroneously to the wrong address.  Please use email for non-clinical issues only and please do not use email or faxes in emergency situations!</p> </div>',3,'2016-09-27 13:42:21',NULL,NULL),(50,'Treatment contract','<div class=\"modal-body\">          <p></p>     <p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Initial Consultation:</b>&nbsp; The first appointment is a 45-60 minute face-to-face assessment. All appropriate intake paperwork must be completed prior to your first appointment.&nbsp; During the first session, the Savant Care provider will obtain a comprehensive history and determine whether our clinic can meet your treatment needs.&nbsp; This session is also an opportunity for both you and the provider to assess your mutual compatibility for an ongoing treatment relationship.&nbsp; Depending on the complexity of your case, a second 45-minute appointment will be made to complete the assessment and make treatment recommendations. Medications may or may not be prescribed during the initial appointment(s).&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"></span><br></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Privacy:</b> Savant Care will not disclose details of your treatment nor your medical record to third parties without your written approval.&nbsp; I work in accordance with the HIPAA laws.&nbsp; You understand your rights under the HIPAA laws can discuss these with me at anytime and have received notice of privacy policies.&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"><b></b></span><br></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Payment:</b> Credit card information or bank information will be obtained prior to your first appointment at Savant Care.&nbsp; You or your payer will be charged at the beginning of each clinic appointment, home visit, and/or in-hospital visit with your Savant Care provider according to the fee structure outlined in the Financial Policies.&nbsp; If you have insurance, then we will charge the appropriate amount. If you seek reimbursement from an insurer, Savant Care can submit claims on your behalf at your request (see Financial Policies for further information).</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"></span><br></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Late, Missed Appointment and Cancellation Policies</b>:&nbsp; Sessions start on time and end on time. If you arrive too late to allow time for proper care, you may be asked to reschedule.&nbsp; If you are more than 15 minutes late to your appointment, you will be asked to reschedule.&nbsp; Missed appointments prevent you from receiving required care and prevent the doctor from providing that care.&nbsp; They also prevent another person from care during that time.&nbsp; As a result, <b>you will be financially responsible for the full session fee if you miss your appointment or fail to cancel your appointment within at least 3 business days of the appointment.</b>&nbsp; If an appointment must be missed for whatever reason, <b>you have the option of rescheduling your appointment within the same week of the missed appointment depending on the doctors availability; in this scenario, you will not be charged for a missed appointment.&nbsp; &nbsp;</b></span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Disclosures:</b> If you are a danger to yourself or others or if I suspect abuse towards a child, disabled adult or the elderly, I am ethically and legally required to report it to the appropriate authorities.</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"></span><br></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Legal Issues:</b> In order to safeguard the process of treatment, our providers do not testify in court.&nbsp; I do not accept gifts from patients nor participate in business deals with patients.&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"></span><br></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Controlled substance policy:</b> Please take extra precaution when handling a prescription of controlled substances (as per DEA definition of a controlled substance) such as Opiates, Stimulants, Sedative-Hypnotic agents etc. We reserve the right to refuse giving early refills or to replace lost prescriptions. If prescriptions are lost or you have run out early more than once in a 1 year period we may decide to discharge you from the clinic if abuse or misuse is suspected.&nbsp; If there is any evidence that you have been receiving controlled prescriptions without informing your Savant Care provider from multiple physicians, we reserve the right to discharge from the clinic immediately. In such case, if you are concerned for your health or safety, you should visit the nearest Emergency or call 911.</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"></span><br></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Clinic discharge policy:</b>&nbsp; Savant Care reserves the right to discharge patients from the clinic under the various conditions including but, not limited to:&nbsp;</span></p><ul>\n<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s2\"></span><span class=\"s1\">multiple missed appointments</span></li>\n<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s2\"></span><span class=\"s1\">patient non-adherence to the treatment plan</span></li>\n<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s2\"></span><span class=\"s1\">non-payment of fee owed to providers of Savant Care</span></li>\n<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s2\"></span><span class=\"s1\">if you fail to follow up with your provider for more than 6 months without prior authorization or have &gt;3 cancellations/missed appointments within a 12 month period, it will be considered failure to comply with the treatment plan and you will be automatically discharged from Savant Care as a patient. You may return to clinic with authorization from a provider and resume receiving care at Savant Care if you wish to do so. if there is any evidence that you have been receiving controlled prescriptions without informing your Savant Care provider from multiple physicians, we reserve the right to discharge from the clinic immediately.</span></li>\n<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s2\"></span><span class=\"s1\">if prescriptions are lost or you have run out early more than once in a 1 year period we may decide to discharge you from the clinic if abuse or misuse is suspected.</span></li>\n<li class=\"li1\"><span class=\"s2\"></span><span class=\"s1\">if there is any evidence that you have been receiving controlled prescriptions from multiple physicians without informing your Savant Care provider, we reserve the right to discharge from the clinic immediately.</span></li>\n</ul><p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"></span><br></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Our clinic policies are subject to change and you will be notified of these changes as they arise. Savant care reserves the right to make changes to clinic policies at any time. This contract will be valid for 3 years. &nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><br><span class=\"s1\"></span></p><p><strong>I understand that I will be financially&nbsp;responsible&nbsp;for the full session fee if I miss my appointment or fail to cancel my intake of follow up appointment withint at least 3 business days of the appointment.&nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong>I have acknowledged the clinic discharge policy outlined above.</strong></p><p><strong><br></strong></p><p><strong><br></strong></p>           </div>',8,'2016-10-06 19:14:45',NULL,NULL),(51,'Privacy policy','<div class=\"modal-body\">      <p>Savant Care works in accordance with the HIPAA laws. These laws protect the confidentiality of all communications between a patient and psychiatrist/psychotherapist.  Several types of communications and the consent they require are discussed below.</p>     <p>     </p><ol type=\"1\">         <li>Generally, information about your treatment can be released to others only if you sign a written Release of Information form.</li>         <li>There are other situations, however, that require only that you provide written, advance consent.  Your signature on this Agreement provides consent for the following:             <ul type=\"i\">                 <li>Your psychiatrist may occasionally find it helpful to consult other health and mental health professionals about a case. During a consultation, every effort is made to avoid revealing your identity.  The other professionals are also legally bound to keep the information confidential.  You will not be told about these consultations unless your therapist feels it is important to your work together</li>                 <li>Savant Care employs other mental health professionals and administrative staff to run the practice.  As a result, some protected information may be shared with these individuals for both clinical and administrative purposes, such as scheduling, billing, and quality assurance. All of the mental health professionals and staff are bound by the same rules of confidentiality and all staff members have undergone the appropriate HIPAA training to protect your privacy.  No staff member will release any information outside of the practice without the permission of a professional staff member.</li><li><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">The mental health professionals on your care team (your Savant Care doctor, your Savant Care therapist, etc) collaborate closely on clinical matters to ensure the best possible care.</span></li>                 <li>Savant Care has contracts with other vendors such as software providers and an accountant.  Typically no protected health information is shared with them. As required by HIPAA laws, we have a formal business associate contract with these outside businesses, in which they promise to maintain the confidentiality of any such data except as specifically allowed in the contract or otherwise required by law.</li>                 <li>Disclosures required by health insurers or to collect overdue fees are discussed in the Financial Policies.</li>                 <li>If your psychiatrist believes that you present an imminent danger to your health or safety, he/she may be obligated to seek hospitalization for you or to contact family members or others who can help provide assistance.</li>             </ul>         </li>         <li>There are also some situations where psychiatrists are permitted or required to disclose information without either your consent or authorization:             <ul type=\"i\">                 <li>If you are involved in a court proceeding and a request is made for information concerning the professional services provided to you, such information is protected by the psychiatrist-patient privilege law.  Information cannot be provided without your written authorization or a court order.  If you are involved in or contemplating litigation, you should consult with your attorney to determine whether a court would be likely to order us to disclose information</li>                 <li>If a government agency is requesting the information for health oversight activities, we may be required to provide it for them</li>                 <li>If a patient files a complaint or a lawsuit against a psychiatrist, that psychiatrist may disclose relevant information regarding that patient in order to defend him/herself.</li>                 <li>If a patient files a worker\'s compensation claim, and services are being compensated through workers compensation benefits, a psychiatrist must, upon appropriate request, provide a copy of the patient\'s record to the patient\'s employer.</li>             </ul>         </li>         <li>In addition, there are some situations in which psychiatrists are legally obligated to take actions which are necessary to attempt to protect others from harm and which may require revealing some information about a patient\'s treatment.             <ul type=\"i\">                 <li>If there is a cause to suspect that a child under 18 is abused or neglected, or reasonable cause to believe that a disabled adult or elderly individual is in need of protective services, the law requires that a report be filed with the county.  Once such a report is filed, additional information may be required.</li>                 <li>If there is reasons to believe that a client present imminent danger to the health and safety of another, we may be required to disclose information in order to take protective actions, including initiating hospitalization, warning the potential victim, if identifiable and or calling the police.</li>             </ul>         </li>     </ol>     <p></p>     <p>The laws governing confidentiality can be quite complex.  It is important that any questions or concerns that you may have now or in the future be discussed. In some cases, formal legal advice may be needed. </p>     <p>Note: Email communication can be relatively easily accessed by unauthorized people, and thus, the privacy and confidentiality of such communication can be easily compromised.  In rare cases, faxes may be sent erroneously to the wrong address.  Please use email for non-clinical issues only and please do not use email or faxes in emergency situations!</p> </div>',4,'2016-11-03 17:17:57',NULL,NULL),(52,'Financial policy','<div class=\"modal-body\">     \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>A. INSURANCE TRACK:</b></span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">The physicians at Savant Care are currently contracted with MHN, Anthem Blue Cross Of California, Blue Shield of California,&nbsp; Aetna, Tricare, Medicare, and Cardinal Care.&nbsp; They are currently accepting new patients.&nbsp; If you are a member of one of these insurances, and are interested in utilizing your coverage for mental health treatment, it is very important that you find out exactly what mental health services your particular policy covers. You should carefully read the section in your insurance coverage booklet that describes mental health services.&nbsp; If you have questions about the coverage, call your plan administrator.&nbsp; Our&nbsp; staff will provide you with assistance in receiving the benefits to which you are entitled; however you (not your insurance company) are responsible for full payment of your bill.&nbsp; If your failure to comply with your insurance companys requirements regarding choice of providers, authorization, or other issues resulting in the denial of claims, you will be responsible for paying in full.&nbsp; If your coverage changes, it is your responsibility to notify your provider and to comply with your new policy.&nbsp; In-Network participation by SC and it\'s providers are subject to change without notice.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Once Savant Care has all of the information about your insurance coverage, your psychiatrist will discuss what you can expect to accomplish with the benefits that are available and what will happen if they run out before you feel ready to end your treatment.&nbsp; It is important to remember that you always have the right to pay for services out of pocket to avoid the potential issues described above (unless this is prohibited by your insurance contract).&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">You should be aware that your insurance company requires a clinical diagnosis and information about the services provided to you.&nbsp; Sometimes, your physician must provide additional clinical information such as treatment plans or summaries, or copies of your entire Clinical Record.&nbsp; In such situations, every effort will be made to release only the minimum information about you that is necessary for the purpose requested.&nbsp; This information will become part of the insurance companys records. Though all insurance companies claim to keep such information confidential, we have no control over what they do with it once it is in their hands. &nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"></span><br></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Initial visits will be 45 minutes.&nbsp; Follow up appointments for medication management will be 15-20 minutes and for psychotherapy +/- medication management will be 45 minutes.&nbsp;</b></span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">It is our policy to charge on a prorated basis for other professional services such as extended telephone consultations, report writing, meeting attendance, disability paperwork, letter writing, and preparation of treatment summaries. You are responsible for any charges not covered by your insurance carrier including any co-payments required by your policy.</span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><span style=\"font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">FOR INSURANCE: IT IS IMPORTANT TO CONTACT OUR OFFICE IMMEDIATELY FOR ANY CHANGES TO YOUR INSURANCE. FAILURE TO ADVISE OF NEW INSURANCE OR POLICIES MAY LEAD YOUR CLAIM TO BE DENIED BY YOUR INSURANCE, AND SC\'S OUT-OF-POCKET RATES WILL BECOME APPLICABLE.&nbsp;</span><br></span></p><p class=\"p1\">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>B. OUT-OF-POCKET TRACK:</b></span></p><table cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"center\" border=\"1\"><thead><tr><th>Encounter Type</th><th>Description</th><th>Fee</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td align=\"center\">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">Intake Appointment(s)</span></p></td><td>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">45-60 minute appointment(s) aimed at gathering historical data about your treatment and life. If your case is complex, you may require 2 intake appointments to allow our doctors to gather the necessary information</span></p><br></td><td align=\"center\">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">$500 for patients ages 18 and older</span></p>\n<p class=\"p2\">$600 for patients ages 0-17<br><span class=\"s1\"></span></p></td></tr><tr><td align=\"center\">Standard Medication Follow-Up</td><td>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">20 minutes face-to-face, 10 minutes for documentation and other management tasks by the provider&nbsp;</span></p></td><td align=\"center\">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">$250 for patients ages 18 and older</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">$300 for patients ages 0-17</span></p></td></tr><tr><td align=\"center\">Standard Psychotherapy Session</td><td>45 minutes face-to-face appointment</td><td align=\"center\">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">$375 for patients ages 18 and older</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">$450 for patients ages 0-17</span></p></td></tr><tr><td align=\"center\">Other</td><td>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">- Telephone calls with provider and email communications with provider requiring significant amounts of time will be treated as consultation with the provider and will be charged as such.<br>\n- Coordination of care on behalf of patient requiring significant amount of time may incur an extra fee</span></p><p class=\"p1\">- Disability documentation and other extraneous documentation will incur an extra fee.&nbsp;</p></td><td align=\"center\">TBD</td></tr><tr><td align=\"center\"><br></td><td><br></td><td align=\"center\"><br></td></tr></tbody></table>     <p></p>     <p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>C. CONCIERGE TRACK: </b>If you choose the Concierge Track, you will be given first priority for appointment times. <b>This means you will have access to the evening and weekend times of our providers, in addition to their regular clinic business hours.</b> You will also have the option of obtaining a home or in-hospital (if admitted) based on necessity within at least 2 business days of your request. You should expect returned phone calls or email responses directly from your provider within at least 4 business hours.</span></p>     <table cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" align=\"center\" border=\"1\">         <thead>             <tr>                 <th>Encounter Type</th>                 <th>Time Spent</th>                 <th>Fee</th>             </tr>         </thead>         <tbody>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Initial Appointment</td>                 <td>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">45-60 minute appointment(s) aimed at gathering historical data about your treatment and life. If your case is complex, you may require 2 intake appointments to allow our doctors to gather the necessary information</span></p></td><td align=\"center\">\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">$800</span></p></td></tr><tr><td align=\"center\">Standard Medication Follow-Up (Phone or In-Clinic)</td>                 <td>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">20 minutes face-to-face, 10 minutes for documentation and other management tasks by the provider&nbsp;</span></p></td><td align=\"center\">$400</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Standard Psychotherapy Session (Phone or In-Clinic)</td>                 <td>45 minutes face-to-face, 15 minutes for documentation by the provider</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$600</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">In-Home or In-Hospital Visits (based on necessity, as deemed appropriate by consulting Psychiatrist)</td>                 <td>45 minute in-home or in-hospital (if admitted) face-to-face visit with provider within 10 mile radius within 2 business days of the request</td>                 <td align=\"center\">$900</td>             </tr>             <tr>                 <td align=\"center\">Other</td>                 <td>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">- Telephone calls with provider and email communications with provider requiring significant amounts of time will be treated as consultation with the provider and will be charged as such.<br>\n- Coordination of care on behalf of patient requiring significant amount of time may incur an extra fee.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">- Disability documentation and other extraneous documentation will incur an extra fee</span></p></td><td align=\"center\">TBD</td>             </tr>         </tbody>     </table>     <p><strong>Note that if you seek reimbursement from an insurer, Savant Care can submit claims on your behalf at your request without any extra charge.</strong>&nbsp;Insurers may only partially reimburse you; contact your insurer for details on your out-of-network coverage. You should be aware that, in order for you to obtain reimbursement, your insurance company requires a clinical diagnosis and information about the services provided to you. Sometimes, your physician must provide additional clinical information such as treatment plans or summaries, or copies of your entire Clinical Record. In such situations, every effort will be made to release only the minimum information about you that is necessary for the purpose requested. This information will become part of the insurance company\'s records. Though all insurance companies claim to keep such information confidential, we have no control over what they do with it once it is in their hands.</p><p><strong>Cancellation Policies: </strong>Sessions start on time and end on time. If you arrive too late to allow time for proper care, you may be asked to reschedule. If you are more than 15 minutes late to your appointment, you will be asked to reschedule. Missed appointments prevent you from receiving required care and prevent the doctor from providing that care. It also prevents another person from receiving care during that time. As a result,&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">you will be financially responsible for $250 cancellation fee if you miss your initial appointment&nbsp;or fail to cancel it within at least 3 business days of the appointment. You will be financially responsible for the full session fee. If you miss a follow up appointment or fail to cancel it within at least 3 business days of the appointment.&nbsp;</span>If an appointment must be missed for whatever reasons,&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">you have the option of rescheduling your appointment <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">within the same week </span>of the missed appointment depending on the doctor\'s&nbsp;availability. In this scenario, you will not be charged for a missed appointment. If you fail to make your rescheduled appointment, you will be billed the cancellation fees for BOTH sessions missed. If you are found to be habitually abusing the cancellation policies (i.e. 5 or more cancellations within a 6 month period), you will be charged additional fees and subject to discharge.</span><br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note: </span>Insurance does NOT cover missed appointments.&nbsp;<br></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Payment Methods:&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;Bank ACH&nbsp;(direct deposit) as this proves to be the lowest cost solution for patients.&nbsp;&nbsp;Credit Cards&nbsp;and&nbsp;Debit Cards&nbsp;are accepted, but any fees charged by your credit card company will be passed to you. As of August 1st,2016, the fee is 4%.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-style: italic;\">CHECKS and CASH are accepted, but are not preferred. If check or cash is provided for payment, a $50 paper check/cash handling fee applies for each check or cash transaction.&nbsp;</span></p><p>All charges to Credit/Debit Cards and ACH are performed up to 3 business days BEFORE your appointment.&nbsp;</p><p>All payments made will first be applied to any prior unpaid balances before current charges.&nbsp;<br></p><p>By providing your details and signing this policy below, you are authorizing Savant Care to charge your account details provided and agree to pay all applicable charges outstanding on your patient account.</p><p>Savant Care may offer treatment at discounted rates if you provide proof of financial need. &nbsp;Please submit your requests to Savant Care\'s finance team. <span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">NOTE:&nbsp;PROVIDERS CAN NOT GRANT DISCOUNTS NOR \'NEGOTIATE\' LOWER RATES WITH PATIENTS.<br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Savant Care and it\'s providers DO NOT accept or participate in MEDI-CAL or MEDICAID programs. If you have this as a secondary insurance, you will be solely responsible for all charges not paid or covered by your primary insurance.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Savant Care is not liable or responsible for any disputes or issues you may have with your insurer concerning your plan\'s deductible, coinsurance, or out-of-pocket limits. It is the patient\'s responsibility to contact their insurance for inquiries or concerns related to their applicable benefits.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Note that if you are having difficulties paying your balance, or feel we may have billed you in error, please contact our office for resolution before initiating action with your financial institution. Failure to notify our office for resolution before initiating a dispute or chargeback will result in a fee of $50 for each&nbsp;occurrence.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Other services:&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">For requests for paperwork that is not available electronically and not from a medical provider (i.e. Explanation of benefits, invoices above and beyond what\'s available on your Myhealth Portal, or research requests for the office staff), a surcharge of $50 will be applied for each occurrence up to 1 hour of office staff\'s time.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-weight: bold;\">An addition fee of $25/hour will be applied beyond the first hour per occurrence.&nbsp;</span></p><p><br></p>  </div>',35,'2016-11-15 15:38:15',NULL,NULL),(53,'Treatment contract','<div class=\"modal-body\">          <p></p>     <p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Initial Consultation:</b>&nbsp; The first appointment is a 45-60 minute face-to-face assessment. All appropriate intake paperwork must be completed prior to your first appointment.&nbsp; During the first session, the Savant Care provider will obtain a comprehensive history and determine whether our clinic can meet your treatment needs.&nbsp; This session is also an opportunity for both you and the provider to assess your mutual compatibility for an ongoing treatment relationship.&nbsp; Depending on the complexity of your case, a second 45-minute appointment will be made to complete the assessment and make treatment recommendations. Medications may or may not be prescribed during the initial appointment(s).&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"></span><br></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Privacy:</b> Savant Care will not disclose details of your treatment nor your medical record to third parties without your written approval. &nbsp;Savant Care operates in accordance with the HIPAA laws.&nbsp; You acknowledge that you understand your rights under the HIPAA laws and can freely discuss these rights with your provider. You also acknowledge you have received notice of the privacy policies.&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Payment:</b> Credit card information or bank information will be obtained prior to your first appointment at Savant Care. &nbsp;You and/or your payer will be charged <span style=\"font-style: italic;\">before</span>&nbsp;each clinic appointment, home visit, and/or in-hospital visit with your Savant Care provider according to the fee structure outlined in the Financial Policies.&nbsp; If you have insurance, Savant Care will charge you the appropriate coinsurance or copayment as derived from your insurance company\'s eligibility database. If after charging for the copayment or coinsurance, Savant Care comes to know through your insurance\'s Explanation of Benefits that the amount due is greater or less than the amount originally charged to you, Savant Care will appropriately bill you for the difference and/or refund the excess to your patient account as applicable. Neither Savant Care nor its\' providers are liable for any copay, coinsurance, or other obligations reported to our office by your insurance company. Should you have questions regarding your coverages, please contact your insurance carrier for details.&nbsp;</span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">&nbsp;If you seek reimbursement from an insurer, Savant Care can submit claims on your behalf at your request (see Financial Policies for further information).</span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Late, Missed Appointment and Cancellation Policies</b>:&nbsp; Sessions start on time and end on time. If you arrive too late to allow time for proper care, you may be asked to reschedule.&nbsp; If you are more than 15 minutes late to your appointment, you will be asked to reschedule.&nbsp; Missed appointments prevent you from receiving required care and prevent the doctor from providing that care.&nbsp; They also prevent another person from care during that time.&nbsp; As a result, <b>you will be financially responsible for the full session fee if you miss your appointment or fail to cancel your appointment within at least 3 business days of the appointment.</b>&nbsp; If an appointment must be missed for whatever reason, <b>you have the option of rescheduling your appointment within the same week of the missed appointment depending on the doctors availability; in this scenario, you will not be charged for a missed appointment.&nbsp; &nbsp;</b></span></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Disclosures:</b> If you are a danger to yourself or others or if a Provider suspect abuse towards a child, disabled adult or the elderly, &nbsp;Providers are ethically and legally required to report it to the appropriate authorities.</span></p><p class=\"p2\"><span class=\"s1\"></span><br></p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>Legal Issues:</b> In order to safeguard the process of treatment, our providers do not testify in court.&nbsp; Providers do not acce