time. As a result, </span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">you will be financially responsible for the appointment as stated in the tables above.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:16pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Note: Insurance does NOT cover missed appointments or late cancellations. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:16pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">D. &nbsp;Payment Methods: </span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;Bank ACH (direct deposit) as this proves to be the lowest cost solution for patients. &nbsp;Credit Cards and Debit Cards are accepted, but any fees charged by your credit card company will be passed on to you. As of August 1st, 2016, the fee is 4%. </span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:italic;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">CHECKS and CASH are accepted, but are not preferred. If check or cash is provided for payment, a $50 paper check/cash handling fee applies for each check or cash transaction. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:16pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">All charges to Credit/Debit Cards and ACH are performed up to 3 business days BEFORE your appointment. All payments made will first be applied to any prior unpaid balances before current charges. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:16pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">By providing your details and signing this policy below, you are authorizing Savant Care to charge your account details provided and agree to pay all applicable charges outstanding on your patient account.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:16pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">E. OTHER: </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:16pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Savant Care may offer treatment at discounted rates if you provide proof of financial need. &nbsp;Please submit your requests to Savant Care\'s finance team. </span><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">NOTE: PROVIDERS CAN NOT GRANT DISCOUNTS NOR \'NEGOTIATE\' LOWER RATES WITH PATIENTS.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:16pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Savant Care and its providers DO NOT accept or participate in MEDI-CAL or MEDICAID programs. If you have this as a secondary insurance, you will be solely responsible for all charges not paid or covered by your primary insurance. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:16pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Savant Care is not liable or responsible for any disputes or issues you may have with your insurer concerning your plan\'s deductible, coinsurance, or out-of-pocket limits. It is the patient\'s responsibility to contact their insurance for inquiries or concerns related to their applicable benefits. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:16pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Note that if you are having difficulties paying your balance, or feel we may have billed you in error, please contact our office for resolution before initiating action with your financial institution. Failure to notify our office for resolution before initiating a dispute or chargeback will result in a fee of $50 for each occurrence. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:16pt;text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 700; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">For requests for paperwork that is not available electronically and not from a medical provider (i.e. Explanation of benefits, invoices above and beyond what\'s available on your MyHealth Portal, or research requests for the office staff), a surcharge of $50 will be applied for each occurrence up to 1 hour of office staff\'s time. An additional fee of $25/hour will be applied beyond the first hour per occurrence. </span><br></p>  </div>',37,'2017-02-13 19:09:26',NULL,NULL),(65,'Privacy policy','<div class=\"modal-body\">      <h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent; text-decoration: none; white-space: pre-wrap; font-weight: 700; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-style: normal; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: large;\">PRIVACY POLICIES</span></h3><h3 dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-align: center;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-3ae6bf65-14ef-4fef-72ad-0f181d635ee8\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 23pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Arial; font-size: large;\">Savant Care works in accordance with the HIPAA laws. These laws protect the confidentiality of all communications between a patient and psychiatrist/psychotherapist.  Several types of communications and the consent they require are discussed below. </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 23pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Arial; font-size: large;\">Generally, information about your treatment can be released to others only if you sign a written Release of Information form.</span></p><ol style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">There are other situations, however, that require only that you provide written, advance consent. Your signature on this Agreement provides consent for the following:</span></p></li><ul style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">Your psychiatrist may occasionally find it helpful to consult other health and mental health professionals about a case. During a consultation, every effort is made to avoid revealing your identity. The other professionals are also legally bound to keep the information confidential. You will not be told about these consultations unless your care provider feels it is important to your work together.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">Savant Care employs other mental health professionals and administrative staff to run the practice. As a result, some protected information may be shared with these individuals for both clinical and administrative purposes, such as scheduling, billing, and quality assurance. All of the mental health professionals and staff are bound by the same rules of confidentiality and all staff members have undergone the appropriate HIPAA training to protect your privacy. No staff member will release any information outside of the practice without the permission of a professional staff member.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-weight: 700; font-size: large;\">The mental health professionals on your care team (your Savant Care doctor, your Savant Care therapist, etc) collaborate closely on clinical matters to ensure the best possible care.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">Savant Care has contracts with other vendors such as software providers and an accountant. Typically no protected health information is shared with them. As required by HIPAA laws, we have a formal business associate contract with these outside businesses, in which they promise to maintain the confidentiality of any such data except as specifically allowed in the contract or otherwise required by law.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline;\"><ul aria-live=\"polite\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 21px 0px 10px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px solid; list-style: none; user-select: none; text-align: start;\"><li id=\"bsfbomowFbegNEnmA\" class=\"message background-transparent-dark-hover\" data-username=\"vidushi.savant\" data-date=\"February 22, 2017\" data-timestamp=\"1487795605795\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 8px 20px 4px 70px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px solid; user-select: none; position: relative; line-height: 20px; min-height: 40px;\"><div class=\"body color-primary-font-color \" dir=\"auto\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin: 2px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px solid; user-select: text; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 1s linear;\"><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Savant Care shall send any and all communications to the email address, mailing/home address and personal phone number that patients use to make an appointment. Savant Care shall not held be responsible for breach of HIPAA if the email or phone number is not the patient\'s and any PHI is passed on to the incorrect recipient due to this.</span></div></li></ul></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: large; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Disclosures required by health insurers or to collect overdue fees are discussed in the Financial Policies.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">If your psychiatrist believes that you present an imminent danger to your health or safety, he/she may be obligated to seek hospitalization for you or to contact family members or others who can help provide assistance.</span></p></li></ul><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">There are also some situations where psychiatrists are permitted or required by law to disclose information without either your consent or authorization:</span></p></li><ul style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">If you are involved in a court proceeding and a request is made for information concerning the professional services provided to you, such information is protected by the psychiatrist-patient privilege law. Information cannot be provided without your written authorization or a court order. If you are involved in or contemplating litigation, you should consult with your attorney to determine whether a court would be likely to order us to disclose information.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">If a government agency is requesting the information for health oversight activities, we may be required to provide it for them.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">If a patient files a complaint or a lawsuit against a psychiatrist, that psychiatrist may disclose relevant information regarding that patient in order to defend him/herself.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">If a patient files a worker\'s compensation claim, and services are being compensated through workers compensation benefits, a psychiatrist must, upon appropriate request, provide a copy of the patient\'s record to the patient\'s employer.</span></p></li></ul><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; list-style-type: decimal; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">In addition, there are some situations in which psychiatrists are legally obligated to take actions which are necessary to attempt to protect others from harm and which may require revealing some information about a patient\'s treatment.</span></p></li><ul style=\"font-weight: normal; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">If there is a cause to suspect that a child under 18 is abused or neglected, or reasonable cause to believe that a disabled adult or elderly individual is in need of protective services, the law requires that a report be filed with the county. Once such a report is filed, additional information may be required.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type: circle; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: Arial;\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.2;margin-top:23pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; font-size: large;\">If there is reasons to believe that a client present imminent danger to the health and safety of another, we may be required to disclose information in order to take protective actions, including initiating hospitalization, warning the potential victim, if identifiable and/or calling the police.</span></p></li></ul></ol><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 23pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Arial; font-size: large;\">The laws governing confidentiality can be quite complex. It is important that any questions or concerns that you may have now or in the future be discussed. In some cases, formal legal advice may be needed.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 23pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"vertical-align: baseline; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Arial; font-size: large;\">Note: Email communication can be relatively easily accessed by unauthorized people, and thus, the privacy and confidentiality of such communication can be easily compromised. You may wish to communicate with your provider via email at your own risk. We do provide a secure way for patients to electronically communicate with their providers, please call our office for more information about this technology. Please use email for non-clinical issues only and please do not use email or faxes in emergency situations! In rare cases, faxes may be sent erroneously to the wrong address. </span></p><div style=\"font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br></span></div></span></h3> </div>',7,'2017-02-22 13:40:19',NULL,NULL),(66,'Pr